The paper presents an algorithm for reinforcement learning in rich observation environments that involves representation learning and strategic exploration. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories related to machine learning and robotics, such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.RO (Robotics), and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Additionally, the paper discusses the sample complexity and computational efficiency of the algorithm, which could also make it relevant to the sub-category cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
